n's work - on and off stage - and autobiography, activism, technique, touring, education and the law. 'Women and popular performance' focuses on the careers of individual artists, once household names, including Lily Brayton, Ellen Terry, radio star Mabel Constanduros and Oscar-winning film star Margaret Rutherford.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 7aHISTORY / Women .2bisacsh  aprofessional networks.  aprofessionalisation.  atheatre historiography.  atheatre.  awomen.1 aBush-Bailey, Gilli, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCockin, Katharine, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDorney, Kate, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDorney, Kate, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aGale, Maggie B., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGale, Maggie B., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aGardner, Viv, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHindson, Catherine, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHolmes, Kate, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKelly, Veronica, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPaxton, Naomi, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSingleton, Brian, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aStokes, John, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSutherland, Lucie, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester Universi